&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desk Command &amp;amp; Editorial Judgment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Run the U.S. news desk during peak coverage hours, making final calls on framing, prioritization, and play. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Distinguish decisively between stories that advance public understanding and those that merely follow the pack. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Kill weak or redundant stories quickly—and demand better replacements. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
